These guns are hard to find, and ones with 30 rounds down the pipe in mint condition are almost impossible to find. Absolutely zero issues, shoots great, and is dead accurate. It has probably the best trigger I've ever encountered on a .22 pistol. These firearms are unique because the barrel sits low, and has a bushing on the end that you can pop off and but a threaded one (like $20) to put on a suppressor. Since the barrel sits so low, no high sights are needed, and they make phenomenal suppressor hosts. The 2206 is also a full stainless steel firearm (slide and frame) which makes recoil laughable. It comes with the original box, manual, 2-10 round magazines, and one orange follower 12-round magazine which is VERY rare and I've seen them list for $80-$140 alone which is crazy for 2 extra rounds.Asking $500. Not interested in trades.Located in Northville, willing to travel a bit but nothing crazy. Face to face in Michigan ONLY. I will not ship. title: For Sale/Trade:  CZ 75 P-01
postcontent:
***Like new CZ 75  P-01.  Only have 500 rounds through it.  Have a few upgrades:  Truglo TFX Pro's ($186), Lok Grips G10 grips ($60), Mid Atlantic Holster ($30).  Comes with original box, manual, grips, 2 mags, lock, cleaning rod, etc.The CZ P-01 is a compact, aluminum-framed 9mm designed for LE and Military duty, but its compact size and the reduced weight due to its forged alloy frame make it ideal for discrete carry as well. Equipped with a decocker, the P-01 provides convenience for those who prefer hammer-down carry. With a heavy first-round trigger pull, any additional shots are a light, crisp single action.
The P-01 was the first CZ model to benefit from updated manufacturing technology at CZ’s Uhersky Brod factory. Since the time of its introduction (designed in 2001, NATO-approved in 2003) the production upgrades have been rolled out to the rest of the CZ 75 family and several new rifle models as well.
These upgrades mean the components of the P-01/P-06 are completely interchangeable with every other P-01/P-06, with no individual fitting needed. This required some very careful re-design so that the reliability and accuracy were not impaired.
With an integral 1913 accessory rail on its dust cover, the P-01 easily accepts any of the industry-standard lights and lasers to assist with low-light use.
After 3 years of some of the most aggressive small arms testing ever, the CZ P-01 won the honor of replacing the CZ 75s previously used by the Czech National Police.
Reliability:  The U.S. Army “Mean Rounds Between Failure” (MRBF) requirement is 495 rounds for 9mm pistols. During testing of the CZ P-01, the average number of stoppages was only 7 per 15,000 rounds fired. This is a .05% failure rate or an MRBF of 2142! For many years, the P-01 carried an NSN engraved on its frame, making it the first NATO-spec pistol ever available to the public. Recently, the factory decided to upgrade the slide stop spring which in turn means the current models may or may not carry an NSN.

title: For Sale:  PATRIOT ORDNANCE FACTORY P308, 20 INCH NEW IN BOX, NICKEL RECEIVER
location: Washington Square Mall area, Portland, Oregon
postcontent: POF P308 CHAMBERED FOR 7.62X51mm NATO / 308 Win.  NEW IN BOX UNFIRED, KEPT IN A SAFE, NEVER A ROUND CHAMBERED, NO SCOPE EVER MOUNTED PATRIOT ORDNANCE P308 NICKEL RECEIVER, 20 INCH BARREL, ATLAS BIPOD NOT INCLUDED, as it was put on the rifle so I could take pictures. These rifles are very much the epitome of what a top tier AR-10 is and should be. They were designed by an aerospace engineer for maximum efficiency. They come with Rock Creek Barrel and that barrel has a chemically induced heat treated finish on the inside (bore) to increase barrel life. POF told me they expect a 100,000 round barrel life from these top of the line Rock Creek Barrels with the nitride coating. The rifles also feature an oversized barrel nut that fastens the barrel to the receiver and it acts as a heat sink drawing heat away from the chamber/receiver area to help the gun run cooler. Also, the gun is piston driven and this keeps the gun running so much cleaner and cooler than a conventional gas impingement AR-10. This resuts in no hot gases with gunpowder residue ending up in the chamber thus heating up the chamber excessively and making it very dirty and cleaning a chore. This gun will operate so much cooler and cleaner than a gas operated AR-10. It saves you time cleaning and your receiver and bolt assmebly last so much longer. There is also a setting on the gas piston  (piston driven gun not gas impingement) for using a suppressor. The rifle also featuers fully ambidextrious controls, and NP3 Nickel finish on the receiver which is just gorgeous, and enough picatinny rails to put whatever you will need on the gun and a quick detach sling fixture on the front left side of the forend. It takes magpul magazines and has Patriot Ordnance's proprietary trigger. POF states the gun should be MOA or better in accuracy, and told me that 0.7 MOA with  good ammo is very common. The rifle's MSRP is $2699 and the do not make it anymore in a 20 inch barrel, and that is too bad becasuse not only can you use it as a main battle rifle, you can also use it as a precision long range AR-10 that will shoot 1,000 yards and beyond with good ammunition. The 20 inch barrel gives you all the velocity to lauch those heavy 175 grain to 190 grain bullets fast enough to shoot 1100 - 1200 yards with control. You can also hunt with this rifle and take down anything that walks on the North American Continent with the right bullet. At 8.9 pounds this rifle is the lightest 20 inch barreled AR-10 on the market, except that these are now getting hard to come by because they are now only made in 18.5 inch and shorter barrels. You give up about 100fps when you drop from a 20 inch barrel to an 18.5 inch one. I've studied this. I'd rather have a 20 incher and get all the perforrmance.  Gun comes in a hard plastic case.
